Papaver bracteatum

   [8292.jpg]
    Authority   Lindley
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Magnoliidae:Ranunculales:Papaveraceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8292

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 294 [USE, TEXT, DRA, DEP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 23 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Rehms S 1991 pp 306 313 [USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial herb. Plants are grown from roots cuttings and flower in
   their 2nd year. Thebaine content is highest 20-30 days after the
   flowers open.
   COMMON NAMES
   Scarlet poppy, Oriental poppy.
   FURTHER INF
   Scarlet poppy is native of Caucasus and northern and western Iran. It
   can be found at elevations between 1500 and 3000 m. Combined yields of
   thebaine are 15-70 kg/ha.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
